section.section:
"Reunderwrite" does not include:
moving an individual from one rate tier to another rate tier solely due to the addition or deletion of a family member under the health coverage;
increasing the premium under an attained age rated contract solely due to the increasing age of the individual covered under the health coverage;
on receipt of an application from an insured to increase the benefits under an existing contract, evaluating the health status-related factors, occupation, hobbies, or activities of the insured for the purpose of increasing the benefits under the contract; or
during the period in which a carrier has the right to contest a policy, denying a claim, amending the policy, making an adjustment to the premium, or rescinding the policy based on a material misrepresentation or fraud in the application.
